snippet.title: Pre-Algebra 2 - Roman Numerals: Sign-Value vs Positional Notation
snippet.description: Roman numerals are an ancient base-10 natural number system. Understanding Roman numerals (a sign-value notation) can shed light on our modern number system which uses positional notation.  NOTE: Please see corrected revision:  https://youtu.be/bqD2wDCiBv0
